    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fiber-like charcoal that occurs in thin layers adjacent to bituminous coal, commonly found in thin silvery-black layers. It is extremely soft and crumbles readily into a fine, sootlike powder.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
